Package models

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
models.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase
extends java.lang.Object
The MemberDatabase class contains a list of all the members of the gym, stored in an array of Member objects. This class also includes methods to print the members based on different sorted fields.
Author:
Jackson Lee, Serena Zeng

      Parameters:

      false if member does not exist, otherwise true

    • print

      public void print()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members is printed without sorting.

    • printByLocation

      public void printByLocation()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by county, then zip code.

    • printByExpirationDate

      public void printByExpirationDate()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by expiration date of membership.

    • printByName

      public void printByName()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by last name, then first name.

    • contains

      Check whether the member database contains the given member

      Returns:
      true if member in database, otherwise false
